Faridabad, Haryana. Agam Kumar Nigam is his father and Sonu's mother's name is Shobha Nigam. Nigam's father belonged to Agra, and he was also a playback singer in Bollywood. Madhurima Nigam is the wife of Sonu Nigam and they were married on 15 February 2002. Nigam has a son whose name is Nevaan. Sonu also has two sisters named Tisha Nigam and Meenal Nigam. Mohammad Rafi was his idol, and he used to dub his singing style on stage shows; for this reason, people often call him modern Rafi. Sonu Nigam completed his schooling at J. D. Tytler School in Delhi and graduated from Delhi University. Singing Career at Early Age When Sonu Nigam was just 4 years old, he used to join stage performances with his father, Agam Kumar Nigam. Slowly he also joined his father at weddings and parties, where they performed together on different songs. Sonu Nigam learnt all his music skills at home from his father. He has grown up by learning every inch of music from him. Sonu's passion for music surpassed every other interest, and later, he pursued this with full focus. He decided to go to Mumbai at 18 with his father to try his luck in the Bollywood music industry. He continued his music training with maestro Ghulam Mustafa Khan and was looking for opportunities. After analyzing his music skills and performances, he considered becoming a playback singer in the Bollywood industry. Sonu Nigam even believed in superstitions, and once he even changed the spelling of his name 'Nigam' to 'Niigaam', he eventually decided to return with the original one. Singing Career Sonu Nigam has recorded devotional, romantic, patriotic, and ghazal songs in various languages like Hindi, Bengali, Gujarati, Nepali, and much more. He has even launched his pop albums and devotional albums in different languages. Nigam's performance is not only limited to India. He has even performed internationally in the countries of Europe, the Middle East, Australia, and Asia. In 2007, Sonu collaborated with 'The Incredibles'.