cess at this time was Kal Ho Naa Ho in 2003. The song was composed by Shankar-Ehsaan-Loy and written by Javed Akhtar. He won two awards for this track. The first was Filmfare Award, and the second was National Film Fare Award for a playback singer in the male category. Sonu Nigam sang four songs with Shreya Ghosal for the movie Parineeta. In 3 Idiots, Sonu Nigam was the leading playback singer. Nigam re-released the album Rafi Ki Yaadein in 2007 in memory of Mohammad Rafi titled Kal Aaj Aur Kal. In 2008 he released Classically Mild and a Punjabi track titled Punjabi Please and Rafi Resurrected. Sonu Nigam even released a song to tribute Michael Jackson after his death. In 2007, Drew Gilpin Faust became the 28th President of Harvard University. There Sonu Nigam sang bhajan during the inauguration programme with Harvard Students. Present Time: 2010-Present time In 2010, Sonu Nigam sang the title track Tees Maar Khan in 54 languages. He also sang the hit song Chori Kiya Re Jiya from the Dabangg. While recording the song Aye Janani, Sonu hit the highest note with open throat effort without using falsetto. In 2010, Sonu Nigam Global Indian Music Academy Awards for the title track All Izz Well. He also won the BIG Star Entertainment Award for best playback singer of the decade. In 2011, Sonu Nigam collaborated with Britney Spears for I Wanna Go and DJ Avicii for Indian Levels. He also wrote and composed the song This Is It. The song was made to tribute Michael Jackson, for which Sonu collaborated with Michael Jackson's brother Jermaine Jackson. Between 2012 and 2015, many of Sonu's songs were redubbed in other singers' voices by music companies because he was fighting for singers' royalties and against the companies' illegal contracts. Sonu said that he wasn't scared of being out because he believed that good sense would prevail in the end. Sonu Nigam also sang the Abhi Mujh Mein Kahin from the movie Agneepath in 2012, which became a huge success and bagged many awards. BIG Star Entertainment Award, 5th Mirchi Music Award, Zee Cine Awards, Times of India Film Awards, 18th and 19th Lions Gold Award and many more. This song also made him a nominee for best playback singer in the male category at Filmfare Awards. Sonu Nigam considers this song one of his best songs to date. In 2013 Sonu composed the title track of the movie Singh Saab The Great and the movies Sooper Se Ooper and Jal. US Billboard Uncharted charts ranked him as the number one artist several times. Sonu's duet with Shreya Ghosal in Love is a Waste of Time and solo in Bhagwaan Hai Kahaan Re Tu received immense love from people. Sapna Jahan from Brothers was also a popular song. In 2015 Sonu Nigam recorded songs with music director Khayyam for the project Gulam Bandhu. He also collaborated with musicians around the globe for Imagine, composed by John Lennon. In 2016 Sonu Nigam released a single named Crazy Dil, in which he featured himself along with his son and other co-actors of Bollywood like Farah Khan, Sunil Grover, Rajkumar Hirani, Kailash Kher and Natalie Di Luccio. He then released another one titled First Date with Jonita Gandhi. Sonu also collaborated with the 6 Pack Band (Transgender Band) for the Sab Rab De Bande song. Tu Hi Na Jaane from Azhar was Sonu's first collab with music composer Amaal Malik. Sonu Nigam did an International collab with Indian-American DJ Kshmr for a song named Underwater. He received the 9th Mirchi Music Award for Indie Pop Song named Aye Jahaan Aasmaan. The song was sung with Shreya Ghosal, an independent song, and the composer was Abhishek Ray. Sonu also sang a song for the movie Raees starring Shah Rukh Khan, which was unfortunately not included in the movie but later, the same was released on YouTube. Sonu also sang the song Aye Zindagi by Vishal Mishra. The song has already had five versions sung by Asha Bhosle, Abhijeet Bhattacharya, Alka Yagnik, Suresh Wadkar and Shaan. Sonu was also featured in Totta with Kainaat Arora. In this 