n Lennon. In 2016 Sonu Nigam released a single named Crazy Dil, in which he featured himself along with his son and other co-actors of Bollywood like Farah Khan, Sunil Grover, Rajkumar Hirani, Kailash Kher and Natalie Di Luccio. He then released another one titled First Date with Jonita Gandhi. Sonu also collaborated with the 6 Pack Band (Transgender Band) for the Sab Rab De Bande song. Tu Hi Na Jaane from Azhar was Sonu's first collab with music composer Amaal Malik. Sonu Nigam did an International collab with Indian-American DJ Kshmr for a song named Underwater. He received the 9th Mirchi Music Award for Indie Pop Song named Aye Jahaan Aasmaan. The song was sung with Shreya Ghosal, an independent song, and the composer was Abhishek Ray. Sonu also sang a song for the movie Raees starring Shah Rukh Khan, which was unfortunately not included in the movie but later, the same was released on YouTube. Sonu also sang the song Aye Zindagi by Vishal Mishra. The song has already had five versions sung by Asha Bhosle, Abhijeet Bhattacharya, Alka Yagnik, Suresh Wadkar and Shaan. Sonu was also featured in Totta with Kainaat Arora. In this song, he collaborated with Meet Bros. Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya, and Kulfi from 102 Not Out became very popular. Sonu Nigam also sang the remake of Badan Pe Sitaare, originally sung by none other than Sonu's idol, i.e. Mohammad Rafi. It's because the movie Fanney Khan had some references related to Mohammad Rafi; therefore, to maintain originality Anil Kapoor requested him to do so, and that is why Sonu agreed. Sonu also revealed that initially, he hesitated as it would tamper with the original song, but at Anil Kapoor's request, he did it. Sonu also sang songs related to social causes like Tik Tik Plastic, whose objective was to nullify the use of plastic as it harms the environment. He then sang an anthem named Mumbai River Anthem to save Mumbai river. In 2021 Sonu Nigam did a UK tour titled Rafi Kishore aur Main, which Grace Entertainmen