which he performs with ease. Many people claim that his style is pretty much similar to the legendary singer Mohammad Rafi and for this reason, Sonu Nigam is often called 'Modern Rafi'. Sonu Nigam has a very sweet and melodious voice and is one of the greatest and most versatile singers in today's era. Till now, Sonu Nigam has sung more than two thousand songs in ten different languages. Sonu Nigam sang every other song in a Bollywood movie during 2010-2011. He has even worked with some most legendary people in the music industry, like Lata Mangeshkar and Khayyam. Early Life and Educational Qualification Singer Sonu Nigam was born on 30 July 1973 in Faridabad, Haryana. Agam Kumar Nigam is his father and Sonu's mother's name is Shobha Nigam. Nigam's father belonged to Agra, and he was also a playback singer in Bollywood. Madhurima Nigam is the wife of Sonu Nigam and they were married on 15 February 2002. Nigam has a son whose name is Nevaan. Sonu also has two sisters named Tisha Nigam and Meenal Nigam. Mohammad Rafi was his idol, and he used to dub his singing style on stage shows; for this reason, people often call him modern Rafi. Sonu Nigam completed his schooling at J. D. Tytler School in Delhi and graduated from Delhi University. Singing Career at Early Age When Sonu Nigam was just 4 years old, he used to join stage performances with his father, Agam Kumar Nigam. Slowly he also joined his father at weddings and parties, where they performed together on different songs. Sonu Nigam learnt all his music skills at home from his father. He has grown up by learning every inch of music from him. Sonu's passion for music surpassed every other interest, and later, he pursued this with full focus. He decided to go to Mumbai at 18 with his father to try his luck in the Bollywood music industry. He continued his music training with maestro Ghulam Mustafa Khan and was looking for opportunities. After analyzing his music skills and performances, he considered becoming a playback singer in the Bollywood industry. Sonu Nigam even believed in superstitions, and once he even changed the spelling of his name 'Nigam' to 'Niigaam', he eventually decided to return with the original one. Singing Career Sonu Nigam has recorded devotional, romantic, patriotic, and ghazal songs in various languages like Hindi, Bengali, Gujarati, Nepali, and much more. He has even launched his pop albums and devotional albums in different languages. Nigam's performance is not only limited to India. He has even performed internationally in the countries of Europe, the Middle East, Australia, and Asia. In 2007, Sonu collaborated with 'The Incredibles'. The Incredible comprised Asha Bhosle, Kailash Kher, Kunal Ganjawala, and Sonu Nigam. He also organized solo concerts in Canada and Germany by the name Simply Sonu. He became the first Indian singer to do so. Starting Career: 1990-1999 Sonu Nigam got his first break as a playback singer in 1990 for a song from the movie Janam. Due to some unavoidable circumstances, the movie wasn't released. He even signed the contract with T-Series, but it was rejected because of S. P. Balasubramaniam. Though his contract was turned down, T-Series owner Gulshan Kumar was impressed by his passion and talent and gave him a chance for a song from the hit movie Bewafa Sanam. 'Achha Sila Diya Tune' song gave him great success in Bollywood Industry, and the song was a hit after which people started noticing and appreciating this young talented singer. In 1993 Sonu Nigam released his first album titled 'Rafi Ki Yaadein'; after that, he sang songs for many movies like Khuddar, Hulchul, Shera, Jeet, Dulhe Raja, Veerta and many more. 'O Aasman Wale' Aaja Meri Jaan was his first release. Before this song, he already had sung many. During his initial days, Nigam struggled because he wasn't getting the opportunity for a playback singer. He did advertisements on radio. Sonu's primary source of income came from stage shows where he sang Rafi's songs. 