s already had five versions sung by Asha Bhosle, Abhijeet Bhattacharya, Alka Yagnik, Suresh Wadkar and Shaan. Sonu was also featured in Totta with Kainaat Arora. In this song, he collaborated with Meet Bros. Main Badhiya Tu Bhi Badhiya, and Kulfi from 102 Not Out became very popular. Sonu Nigam also sang the remake of Badan Pe Sitaare, originally sung by none other than Sonu's idol, i.e. Mohammad Rafi. It's because the movie Fanney Khan had some references related to Mohammad Rafi; therefore, to maintain originality Anil Kapoor requested him to do so, and that is why Sonu agreed. Sonu also revealed that initially, he hesitated as it would tamper with the original song, but at Anil Kapoor's request, he did it. Sonu also sang songs related to social causes like Tik Tik Plastic, whose objective was to nullify the use of plastic as it harms the environment. He then sang an anthem named Mumbai River Anthem to save Mumbai river. In 2021 Sonu Nigam did a UK tour titled Rafi Kishore aur Main, which Grace Entertainment presented. The show was just wow not only because of Sonu Nigam but also because there were very talented musicians, even some of them from the original composition. He sang his tracks along with the legendary singer's track like Kishore Kumar and Mohammad Rafi, which made the audience glued to their seats for almost four hours. Sonu Nigam has even launched his NFT collection, which consists of some key moments of his life and some details about recordings. He is also the first Indian singer to perform this initiative. Music Label Company I Believe Music is Sonu Nigam's own music label company which was launched on 30 July 2020. The first track released under this label was Rudhrashtakam. Host and Reality Show Judge From 1995 to 1999, Sonu Nigam was the host of the reality music show named Sa Re Ga Ma. Sonu Nigam was also the host of Kitna Hai Dum's show in 2002. In Indian Idol season 1 and 2 Sonu became one of the judges of the show. In seasons 3, 4 and 6, he